# SumoSized SVG Maker: Media Pipeline Architecture

The media pipeline has been refactored for professional performance, reliability, and SvelteKit 5 compliance. This document explains the new architecture and the redistribution of logic.

## 🏗️ Architecture Breakdown

The original monolithic [mediaService.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/services/mediaService.ts) (~300 lines) has been decomposed into specialized modules. This improves maintainability and allows for hardware acceleration.

### 1. [exportService.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/services/exportService.ts) (The Orchestrator)
- **Role**: High-level API for all exports (Static & Animated).
- **Function**: Handles frame capture timing, progress reporting, and selects the best encoder backend.
- **Location**: [exportService.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/services/exportService.ts)

### 2. [media/encoder.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/media/encoder.ts) (The Abstraction)
- **Role**: Common interface for all encoding backends.
- **Function**: Feature-detects capabilities (WebCodecs vs FFmpeg) and exports the correct backend instance.
- **Location**: [encoder.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/media/encoder.ts)

### 3. [media/webcodecsEncoder.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/media/webcodecsEncoder.ts) (Hardware Express)
- **Role**: Hardware-accelerated MP4/WebM/MOV encoding.
- **Function**: Uses the browser's native [VideoEncoder](file:///d:/SVG/node_modules/mediabunny/dist/modules/src/media-source.js#143-532) API. Up to **50x faster** than WASM.
- **Location**: [webcodecsEncoder.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/media/webcodecsEncoder.ts)

### 4. [media/ffmpegEncoder.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/media/ffmpegEncoder.ts) (The Heavy Lifter)
- **Role**: Software fallback and high-quality GIF generator.
- **Function**: Wraps `FFmpeg.wasm` into the standard encoder interface.
- **Location**: [ffmpegEncoder.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/media/ffmpegEncoder.ts)

### 5. [services/mediaService.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/services/mediaService.ts) (The Provider)
- **Role**: FFmpeg instance management.
- **Function**: Handles the logic for loading FFmpeg-core assets from local same-origin paths (`/ffmpeg`).
- **Reduction**: Now only ~45 lines, focusing purely on instance lifecycle.
- **Location**: [mediaService.ts](file:///d:/SVG/src/lib/services/mediaService.ts)

## 🚀 Key Improvements

| Feature | Old System | New System |
|---------|------------|------------|
| **MP4 Performance** | Software (Slow) | Hardware (Instant) |
| **GIF Quality** | Single-pass | Two-pass Palette |
| **CORS/COI** | `coi-serviceworker` | Native Headers |
| **Asset Loading** | Remote CDN | Local (Same-Origin) |
| **Router Sync** | Native History | SvelteKit Navigation |

